        "description": "You try to interrupt a creature in the process of casting a spell. The creature makes a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, the spell fizzles with no effect, and the action, Bonus Action, or Reaction used to cast it is wasted. If the interrupted spell used a spell slot, that slot is not expended."
